{"text": "This used to be my favorite game of all time. Not anymore ______________________________________ The current state of Team Fortress 2 right now is BAD You will see cheaters/hackers in casual matches and maybe competitive too The only way to play this game is by community servers, which I usually don't like them, because most of them have confusing plugins, level system, or even custom sounds and custom effects. If you're a new player, I suggest finding a good community server you are comfortable in and do NOT play casual mode as it is bombarded with hackers and VAC doesn't do anything. The community of Team Fortress 2 has also gotten worse. It is rare to find a FRIENDLY player nowadays and it is unwelcoming to new players, perhaps the in-game tutorial was not enough to teach them advanced techniques (Rocket Jumping, Sticky Jumping, etc). At last, I do not recommend to play this game, for now. You will face a lot of hackers if you play it right now. When Valve fixes the current issues, feel free to play this game!", "appid": "440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198369212102", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595937600.0}
